{"type":"session_message","session_id":"ses_28903e0eaffe1rbjxazpgACW1i","role":"assistant","message_id":"msg_d76fc32590018XXJl8mSWlwV95","parts":[{"id":"prt_d76fc3d86001cD3aJnNlRh2oyx","messageID":"msg_d76fc32590018XXJl8mSWlwV95","sessionID":"ses_28903e0eaffe1rbjxazpgACW1i","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_73fc3c6a43834bb5b5db168d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/workspace/README.md"},"output":"<path>/workspace/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: <div align=\"center\">\n2:   <picture>\n3:     <source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\" srcset=\"https://github.com/reagento/adaptix/blob/v3.0.0b6/docs/logo/adaptix-with-title-dark.png?raw=true\">\n4:     <source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\" srcset=\"https://github.com/reagento/adaptix/blob/v3.0.0b6/docs/logo/adaptix-with-title-light.png?raw=true\">\n5:     <img alt=\"adaptix logo\" src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/reagento/adaptix/v3.0.0b2/docs/logo/adaptix-with-title-light.png?raw=true\">\n6:   </picture>\n7: \n8:   <hr>\n9: \n10:   [![PyPI version](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/adaptix.svg?color=blue)](https://pypi.org/project/adaptix/)\n11:   [![downloads](https://img.shields.io/pypi/dm/adaptix.svg)](https://pypistats.org/packages/adaptix)\n12:   [![versions](https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/adaptix.svg)](https://github.com/reagento/adaptix)\n13:   [![license](https://img.shields.io/github/license/reagento/dataclass_factory.svg)](https://github.com/reagento/adaptix/blob/master/LICENSE)\n14: </div>\n15: \n16: An extremely flexible and configurable data model conversion library.\n17: \n18: > [!IMPORTANT]\n19: > Adaptix is ready for production!\n20: > The beta version only means there may be some backward incompatible changes, so you need to pin a specific version.\n21: \n22: 📚 [Documentation](https://adaptix.readthedocs.io/)\n23: \n24: ## TL;DR\n25: \n26: Install\n27: ```bash\n28: pip install adaptix==3.0.0b12\n29: ```\n30: \n31: Use for model loading and dumping.\n32: \n33: ```python\n34: from dataclasses import dataclass\n35: \n36: from adaptix import Retort\n37: \n38: \n39: @dataclass\n40: class Book:\n41:     title: str\n42:     price: int\n43: \n44: \n45: data = {\n46:     \"title\": \"Fahrenheit 451\",\n47:     \"price\": 100,\n48: }\n49: \n50: # Retort is meant to be global constant or just one-time created\n51: retort = Retort()\n52: \n53: book = retort.load(data, Book)\n54: assert book == Book(title=\"Fahrenheit 451\", price=100)\n55: assert retort.dump(book) == data\n56: ```\n57: \n58: Use for converting one model to another.\n59: \n60: ```python\n61: from dataclasses import dataclass\n62: \n63: from sqlalchemy.orm import DeclarativeBase, Mapped, mapped_column\n64: \n65: from adaptix.conversion import get_converter\n66: \n67: \n68: class Base(DeclarativeBase):\n69:     pass\n70: \n71: \n72: class Book(Base):\n73:     __tablename__ = 'books'\n74: \n75:     id: Mapped[int] = mapped_column(primary_key=True)\n76:     title: Mapped[str]\n77:     price: Mapped[int]\n78: \n79: \n80: @dataclass\n81: class BookDTO:\n82:     id: int\n83:     title: str\n84:     price: int\n85: \n86: \n87: convert_book_to_dto = get_converter(Book, BookDTO)\n88: \n89: assert (\n90:     convert_book_to_dto(Book(id=183, title=\"Fahrenheit 451\", price=100))\n91:     ==\n92:     BookDTO(id=183, title=\"Fahrenheit 451\", price=100)\n93: )\n94: ```\n95: \n96: ## Use cases\n97: \n98: * Validation and transformation of received data for your API.\n99: * Conversion between data models and DTOs.\n100: * Config loading/dumping via codec that produces/takes dict.\n101: * Storing JSON in a database and representing it as a model inside the application code.\n102: * Creating API clients that convert a model to JSON sending to the server.\n103: * Persisting entities at cache storage.\n104: * Implementing fast and primitive ORM.\n105: \n106: ## Advantages\n107: \n108: * Sane defaults for JSON processing, no configuration is needed for simple cases.\n109: * Separated model definition and rules of conversion\n110:   that allow preserving [SRP](https://blog.cleancoder.com/uncle-bob/2014/05/08/SingleReponsibilityPrinciple.html)\n111:   and have different representations for one model.\n112: * Speed. It is one of the fastest data parsing and serialization libraries.\n113: * There is no forced model representation, adaptix can adjust to your needs.\n114: * Support [dozens](https://adaptix.readthedocs.io/en/latest/loading-and-dumping/specific-types-behavior.html) of types,\n115:   including different model kinds:\n116:   ``@dataclass``, ``TypedDict``, ``NamedTuple``,\n117:   [``attrs``](https://www.attrs.org/en/stable/), [``sqlalchemy``](https://docs.sqlalchemy.org/en/20/),\n118:   [``pydantic``](https://docs.pydantic.dev/latest/) and [``msgspec``](https://jcristharif.com/msgspec/).\n119: * Working with self-referenced data types (such as linked lists or trees).\n120: * Saving [path](https://adaptix.readthedocs.io/en/latest/loading-and-dumping/tutorial.html#error-handling)\n121:   where an exception is raised (including unexpected errors).\n122: * Machine-readable [errors](https://adaptix.readthedocs.io/en/latest/loading-and-dumping/tutorial.html#error-handling)\n123:   that could be dumped.\n124: * Support for user-defined generic models.\n125: * Automatic name style conversion (e.g. `snake_case` to `camelCase`).\n126: * [Predicate system](https://adaptix.readthedocs.io/en/latest/loading-and-dumping/tutorial.html#predicate-system)\n127:   that allows to concisely and precisely override some behavior.\n128: * Disabling additional checks to speed up data loading from trusted sources.\n129: * No auto casting by default. The loader does not try to guess value from plenty of input formats.\n\n(End of file - total 129 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"<div align=\"center\">\n  <picture>\n    <source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\" srcset=\"https://github.com/reagento/adaptix/blob/v3.0.0b6/docs/logo/adaptix-with-title-dark.png?raw=true\">\n    <source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\" srcset=\"https://github.com/reagento/adaptix/blob/v3.0.0b6/docs/logo/adaptix-with-title-light.png?raw=true\">\n    <img alt=\"adaptix logo\" src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/reagento/adaptix/v3.0.0b2/docs/logo/adaptix-with-title-light.png?raw=true\">\n  </picture>\n\n  <hr>\n\n  [![PyPI version](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/adaptix.svg?color=blue)](https://pypi.org/project/adaptix/)\n  [![downloads](https://img.shields.io/pypi/dm/adaptix.svg)](https://pypistats.org/packages/adaptix)\n  [![versions](https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/adaptix.svg)](https://github.com/reagento/adaptix)\n  [![license](https://img.shields.io/github/license/reagento/dataclass_factory.svg)](https://github.com/reagento/adaptix/blob/master/LICENSE)\n</div>\n\nAn extremely flexible and configurable data model conversion library.\n\n> [!IMPORTANT]\n> Adaptix is ready for production!\n> The beta version only means there may be some backward incompatible changes, so you need to pin a specific version.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"README.md","time":{"start":1775817735933,"end":1775817735945}}}]}
